Benguet, Digital, JG, Security Bank: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T00:36:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/benguet-digital-jg-security-bank-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.2 percent to
3,907.23.  Benguet Corp. (BCB)  : The mining company had 2.4 billion
pesos ($55 million) in profit last year, a stock exchange filing
showed, without giving a comparative figure. Benguet’s Class A
shares, which only Filipinos can own, increased 1.1 percent to
13 pesos. Its Class B shares (BCB PM), which have no ownership
restrictions, fell 1 percent to 14.20 pesos.  Digital Telecommunications  Philippines  Inc. (DGTL PM):
 Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , the nation’s
largest phone company, offered to buy Digital Telecom in a
transaction valued at 74.1 billion pesos.  Digital Telecom, which voluntarily suspended trading
yesterday before the announcement, rose 18 percent to 1.83 pesos
when it last traded on March 28.  JG Summit Holdings Inc. (JGS)  , owner of Digital Telecom and which also suspended its
trading yesterday, advanced 8.2 percent to 24.50 pesos when it
last traded March 28. Philippine Telephone was unchanged at
2,036 pesos.  Globe Telecom Inc. (GLO)  : The Philippines’ second-
largest mobile phone company is “ready to compete” and
“defend and grow” its market share, President Ernest Cu said
in an e-mailed statement after Philippine Long Distance offered
to buy Digital Telecom. The stock jumped 7 percent to 746 pesos.  Security Bank Corp. (SECB)  : The bank will pay 1 peso a
share in regular and special dividends, a stock exchange filing
showed. The bank will also pay a 20 percent stock dividend, it
said. The stock fell 0.1 percent to 82.45 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
